ses|last=Elsworthy|first=Emma|date=10 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>and a man in his 70s in Tasmania.<ref name=\":8\" />\n*11 April: There were two deaths. One was a man  in Victoria in his 80s, and a 91-year-old woman in New South Wales.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/news/Pages/20200411_00.aspx |title=COVID-19 (Coronavirus) statistics |date=11 April 2020| website=NSW Health |language=en-AU|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n*12 April: There were three deaths. One died in SA, a 74-year-old man who had been a passenger on the ''Ruby Princess'', a second in New South Wales, and a third a woman in her 70s in Tasmania.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*13 April: There were two deaths. A 74-year-old woman and a 79-year-old man who were both passengers on the ''Ruby Princess'' both died in New South Wales. {{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*14 April: There was one death, a 91-year-old woman in Tasmania.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tasmania confirms 91yo woman is sixth coronavirus death |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-14/tasmania-coronavirus-sixth-death/12147964 |website=ABC News |date=14 April 2020 |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n*15 April: There was one death, a woman from the ACT in her 60s who was a passenger on the ''Ruby Princess''.<ref name=\"abc-15-4-20\">{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-15/third-coronavirus-death-in-canberra/12150262 |title=Ruby Princess passenger becomes third Canberra coronavirus death|newspaper=[[ABC News (Australia)]]|date=15 April 2020|accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n*17 April: There were two deaths. One was ship crewman in his 40s on the ''Artania'' who died in WA.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-17/man-in-40s-youngest-to-die-in-australia-from-coronavirus/12159454|title=Artania cruise ship crewman in his 40s becomes youngest person in Australia to die from coronavirus|publisher=